      "content": "Combining garlic and kale juice may have some potential benefits, but combining it with warfarin is unadvisable, as it may interact negatively and increase the risk of bleeding. There's no established dosing for garlic as a replacement for warfarin; even Chinese studies on traditional garlic diets have shown varying results and possible undertreatment or overdosing risks",
      "source": "target",
